"title": "5841: ecstasy",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5841",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An exalted condition of spiritual joy or rapture; usually reflecting the experience of the Holy Spirit.</p>\n<h2>Ecstasy in response to prophetic and visionary experiences</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:4\">NUM 24:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:3-2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:3–12:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:10\">REV 1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:16\">NUM 24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:10-1Sam10:11\">1SA 10:10–10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a> <em>Isaiah's vision of the Lord</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:24-Ezek11:25\">EZK 11:24–11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:19-Dan2:21\">DAN 2:19–2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:7-Dan10:8\">DAN 10:7–10:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:16\">DAN 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:10\">ACT 9:10</a> <em>Ananias' vision</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:3\">ACT 10:3</a> <em>Cornelius' vision of the angel of God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:10-Acts10:16\">ACT 10:10–10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:5\">ACT 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:2\">REV 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3\">REV 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:10\">REV 21:10</a></p>\n<h2>Ecstasy in response to the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:4\">ACT 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts10:46\">ACT 10:44–10:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:52\">ACT 13:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:6\">ACT 19:6</a></p>\n<h2>Ecstasy in response to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:8\">1PE 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:7\">PSA 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:8\">MAT 28:8</a></p>\n<h2>Ecstasy as a corporate experience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:12\">EZR 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:11\">1KI 8:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:2\">2CH 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:16\">EZR 6:16</a></p>\n<h2>Transfiguration of appearance through ecstasy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29\">EXO 34:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:2\">MAT 17:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:22\">LUK 1:22</a></p>\n<h2>Future ecstasy in response to God's coming kingdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:12\">ISA 55:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:9–2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a></p>",
